Package org.eclipse.mosaic.fed.output.ambassador

Class AbstractOutputGenerator

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.mosaic.fed.output.ambassador.AbstractOutputGenerator
Direct Known Subclasses:
FileOutput, WebsocketVisualizer
public class AbstractOutputGenerator extends Object
This class needs to be implemented to add a output generator or visualizer to theOutputAmbassador. The AbstractOutputGenerator holds a registry which redirects subclasses of Interaction to a registered consumer method by its type id (i.e. Interaction.getTypeId(). All interactions which can not be redirected to such method, due to missing registration, is passed to handleUnregisteredInteraction(Interaction).

Each output generator can register specific methods, which are called whenever an interaction with a suitable type id is passed to this output generator. This can be achieved, by adding new methods with exactly one parameter to the sub class implementation, and annotate this method with @Handle: 
 @Handle
 public void handleVehicleUpdates(VehicleUpdates interaction) {
    ...
 }
This works for all subclasses of message, which have a public static member TYPE_ID. If this member is not present (e.g. for custom messages), the annotation can be extended accordingly: 
  @Handle("MyInteraction")
  public void handleMyInteraction(MyInteraction interaction) {
     ...
  }
As a third method, the registerInteractionForOutputGeneration(String, java.util.function.Consumer) method can be used in the constructor. 
  MyOutputGenerator() {
      super();
      registerInteractionForOutputGeneration("MyInteraction", this::handleMyInteraction);
  }

  public void handleMyInteraction(MyInteraction interaction) {
     ...
  }
